                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="addamsfamily_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a family of strange but funny cartoon characters who live in a large dark house and behave in an unusual way that suggests evil and death. They were created in 1935 in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-new-yorker#the_new_yorker_topg_1" title="New Yorker definition"><span class="ndv">New Yorker</span></a> magazine by Charles Addams. The characters were used for television series, and three films (1991, 1993 and 1998).</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
